==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perpetuate
<hw>Per*pet"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Perpetuated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Perpetuating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>perpetuatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>perpetuare</ets> to perpetuate. See <er>Perpetual</er>.]</ety> <def>To make perpetual; to cause to endure, or to be continued, indefinitely; to preserve from extinction or oblivion; to eternize.</def>  <rj><au>Addison.</au>  <au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perpetuate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Perpetuate
<hw>Per*pet"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perpetuatus</ets>, p. p.]</ety> <def>Made perpetual; perpetuated.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>  <rj><au>Southey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perpetuation</ent>⟦br⟧
